@startuml sequence_render
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title BarrelGenerator.Render - Classification, Pairing, Templating

participant "Caller\n(provide handler\nor unit test)" as C
participant "BarrelGenerator" as BG
participant "StringBuilder" as SB

C -> BG : Render("dashboard-state",\n[\n  "dashboard-state-store.contract.ts",\n  "dashboard-state.store.ts",\n  "wall-clock-tick-service.contract.ts",\n  "wall-clock-tick.service.ts",\n  "dashboard-state.model.ts",\n  "chart-visible-window.ts"\n])

note over BG
  Validate folderName
  matches kebab regex.
end note

note over BG
  Classify each name:
  *.contract.ts        -> Contract
  *.store.ts           -> Implementation(Store)
  *.service.ts         -> Implementation(Service)
  *.model.ts           -> Model
  anything else        -> Other (drop)
end note

note over BG
  Derive symbols:
  Contract dashboard-state-store
    -> token DASHBOARD_STATE_STORE
    -> iface IDashboardStateStore
    -> commonBase "dashboard-state"
  Impl dashboard-state.store
    -> class DashboardStateStore
    -> commonBase "dashboard-state"
  (analogous for wall-clock-tick)
end note

note over BG
  Pair by commonBase:
  ("dashboard-state",
   DASHBOARD_STATE_STORE
   <-> DashboardStateStore)
  ("wall-clock-tick",
   WALL_CLOCK_TICK_SERVICE
   <-> WallClockTickService)
  Orphans -> Warning log.
end note

BG -> SB : Append imports + exports + provideXxx body
note right
  Sort impls / contracts / models
  by source file name.
  Sort provider array entries
  by class name then by token name.
  Use \n line endings throughout.
end note
SB --> BG : content string

BG --> C : GeneratedFile {\n  Filename = "index.ts",\n  Content  = "..." \n}

== Empty folder ==

C -> BG : Render("empty-feature", [])
note over BG
  No files. Return:
  import + blank +
  provideEmptyFeature() {
    return [];
  }
end note
BG --> C : GeneratedFile { ... }

== Invalid folder name ==

C -> BG : Render("Bad Name", [...])
BG --> C : throw InvalidFolderNameException

@enduml
